It's about the documentation for `With`. Unless I am wrong, the example code for "With Lombok" on page: https://projectlombok.org/features/With that currently looks like this:

```java
  public WithExample(String name, int age) {
    if (name == null) throw new NullPointerException();
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
  }
```

could be improved by just making `String name` argument `@NonNull`. That should automatically remove the need of check code, so it could look like this:

```java
  public WithExample(@NonNull String name, int age) {
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
  }
```

**Describe the feature**
Extend the @Getter Annotation by a switch to modify the Getter when the type is MutableLiveData<Type>.

@Getter
private final MutableLiveData<Boolean> aMutable = new MutableLiveData<>(true);

should lead to :
LiveData<Boolean> getAMutable(){return aMutable;}
instead of
MutableLiveData<Boolean> getAMutable(){return aMutable;}

Because with LiveData we almost always never want to expose the mutable version of it

**Describe the target audience**
Within Android Apps LiveData is very common

